  note top of GovernorControllerMechanism
    A governor controller mechanism defines and owns policies that guide the
    overall behavior of the system it governs, via supervisor mechanisms
    receiving these policy events and operationalizing these policies as rules.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A governor controller mechanism MUST own at least one policy.
    - Policies associated with a governor controller mechanism MUST be unique
      within the context of that mechanism.
  end note

  ControllerMechanism <|-- GovernorControllerMechanism : is
