  class SensorMechanism

  note top of SensorMechanism
    A sensor mechanism is an observation mechanism on actuations.

    Sensor mechanisms are typically auto-defined from a Sensing linked to an
    Actuation, and only when a control feedback receptor exists.

    **Auto Definition Rules**:
    - For every event archetype E whose schema is a subtype of
      ActuationEventSchema, the sensor mechanism MUST have (or derive) a
      receptor bound to E.
    - For every receptor bound to E, the sensor mechanism MUST have an
      effector bound to event O whose schema is subtype of
      ActuationFeedbackEventSchema.
  end note

